    <div class="description-contents">
      <p>Rated 4/5 on Goodreads; the criticism being that it's too
      slow; that it does not use C-style syntaxed languages.</p>
      <p>In essence, if you find HTDP too easy, you may want to try
      out Structure and Interpretation of Computer Programs; this
      has been praised multiple times on multiple places including
      softwareengineering.stackexchange.</p>
      <p>SICP was in use as a textbook for an introductory(!)
      programming course (6.001) at MIT until 2009 from 1980s(!);
      and is still used, albeit for a more advanced 6.037.</p>
